<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="model"><code>Model::BeekeepingModel</code></h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <p><strong>File:</strong> <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/BeekeepingModel.pm</code></p>
        <p>Catalyst model (<code>extends 'Catalyst::Model'</code>) providing yard and hive-list helpers for the Beekeeping controller hierarchy. Inspection and queen-assignment helpers remain in <code>ApiaryModel</code>.</p>

        <h3>Methods</h3>
        <table class="data-table">
            <thead>
                <tr><th>Method</th><th>Signature</th><th>Returns</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>get_yards_for_site</code></td>
                    <td><code>($self, $c, $sitename)</code></td>
                    <td>ArrayRef of <code>Beekeeping::Yard</code> rows, ordered by <code>yard_name</code></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>get_hives_for_yard</code></td>
                    <td><code>($self, $c, $yard_id)</code></td>
                    <td>ArrayRef of <code>Beekeeping::Hive</code> rows, ordered by <code>hive_name</code></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><code>create_yard</code></td>
                    <td><code>($self, $c, \%params)</code></td>
                    <td><code>(1, undef)</code> on success; <code>(0, $error_string)</code> on failure</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>All methods use <code>$c->model('DBEncy')</code> to access the database and wrap DB calls in <code>eval</code> with <code>warn</code> on error.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="templates">Templates</h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <p>All templates live under <code>root/Beekeeping/</code> and comply with the theme system (use <code>app-container</code>, <code>app-section</code>, <code>content-section</code> CSS classes — see <a href="/Documentation/ApplicationTtTemplate">ApplicationTtTemplate</a>).</p>
        <table class="data-table">
            <thead>
                <tr><th>Template</th><th>Route</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/apiary.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/apiary</code></td><td>Feature overview for guests — yards, inspections, queen rearing, health, bee pasture. CTAs for signup and membership.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/queens.tt</code></td><td>Guest queen info (not directly routed yet)</td><td>Graft calendar form and queen rearing overview</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/health.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/health</code></td><td>Bee health information page</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/harvest.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/harvest</code></td><td>Honey production guide</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/environment.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/environment</code></td><td>Environmental planning — climate, agricultural practices, habitat, bee pasture planning</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/education.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/education</code></td><td>Education hub — bee biology, diseases, hive management, queen rearing, workshops</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/products.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/products</code></td><td>Honey, pollen, beeswax, propolis, royal jelly — products and member advertising</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/Yards/index.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/yards</code></td><td>Yard list table with link to <code>/Apiary/hives_for_yard/:id</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>Beekeeping/Yards/add.tt</code></td><td><code>/Beekeeping/add_yard</code></td><td>Add-yard form with AI form assistant partial</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="design-patterns">Design Patterns</h2>
    <div class="content-section">

        <h3>Guest / member routing split</h3>
        <p>Pages that serve different content to guests vs members implement the following pattern in the controller action:</p>
        <pre class="code-block">if ($c->session->{user_id}) {
    $c->response->redirect($c->uri_for('/Apiary'));
} else {
    $c->stash(template => 'Beekeeping/apiary.tt');
}</pre>
        <p>Guest-facing templates include membership CTAs. Member-facing content lives exclusively in <code>Controller::Apiary</code>.</p>

        <h3>Standard action boilerplate</h3>
        <pre class="code-block">sub my_action :Path('/Beekeeping/my-route') :Args(0) {
    my ($self, $c) = @_;
    $c->stash->{debug_errors} = [] unless defined $c->stash->{debug_errors};
    $self->logging->log_with_details($c, 'info', __FILE__, __LINE__, 'my_action', "called");
    $c->stash(
        template  => 'Beekeeping/my-template.tt',
        debug_msg => 'Page Title',
    );
}</pre>

        <h3>Sub-controller pattern</h3>
        <p>Feature groups with multiple routes get their own sub-controller file in <code>Controller/Beekeeping/</code>. Each uses <code>:Path('/Beekeeping/...')</code> absolute path attributes — no chaining to the Beekeeping base — for simplicity and discoverability.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="app-section">
    <h2 id="extending">Extending the System</h2>
    <div class="content-section">
        <h3>Adding a new public info page</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Add an action to <code>Controller::Beekeeping</code> using <code>:Path('/Beekeeping/your-route') :Args(0)</code>.</li>
            <li>Create <code>root/Beekeeping/your-template.tt</code> — start with <code>[% META title = "..." %]</code>, wrap content in <code>app-container</code> / <code>app-section</code>.</li>
            <li>Link it from <code>root/Navigation/TopDropListBeekeeping.tt</code> if it belongs in the menu.</li>
            <li>Update <code>root/Documentation/BMaster.tt</code> route table.</li>
            <li>Run <code>perl -cw Comserv/script/comserv_server.pl</code>.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Adding a new member management feature</h3>
        <p>Member tools go in <code>Controller::Apiary</code>, not here. Add the route under <code>/Apiary/*</code> and link it from the <code>logged_in</code> branch of <code>TopDropListBeekeeping.tt</code>.</p>

        <h3>Adding a new sub-controller</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Create <code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Beekeeping/MyFeature.pm</code> with <code>package Comserv::Controller::Beekeeping::MyFeature</code>.</li>
            <li>Use <code>BEGIN { extends 'Catalyst::Controller'; }</code>.</li>
            <li>Define actions with absolute <code>:Path('/Beekeeping/my-feature/...')</code> attributes.</li>
            <li>Create templates in <code>root/Beekeeping/MyFeature/</code>.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>File locations summary</h3>
        <table class="data-table">
            <thead>
                <tr><th>Type</th><th>Location</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Controllers</td><td><code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Beekeeping/</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Templates</td><td><code>Comserv/root/Beekeeping/</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Model</td><td><code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/BeekeepingModel.pm</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>DB Result classes</td><td><code>Comserv/lib/Comserv/Model/Schema/Ency/Result/Beekeeping/</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Navigation menu</td><td><code>Comserv/root/Navigation/TopDropListBeekeeping.tt</code></td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>

